title: Toddler Tuesdays at Discovery Green
address: 1500 Mckinney St Houston, TX 77010 United States
body: Bring your toddler to Discovery Green park to enjoy a new storybook and activities each week. Admission: Free.

title: Theater District Food Truck Tuesdays
body: Theater District Houston kicks off another tasty season of Food Truck Tuesdays. Enjoy a rotating cast of local food trucks week in and week out in downtown’s scenic Theater District. Admission: Free.

title: Oktoberfest at Charivari
address: 2521 Bagby St. Houston, TX 77006 United States
body: Oktoberfest celebrations have begun at Charivari Restaurant, where guests can find a special daily lunch and dinner featuring dishes like weissewurst, jaeger schnitzel and obazda, a Bavarian cheese specialty served with pretzel.

title: Yoga at Levy Park
body: Relax your body and mind at an evening yoga class by the Joy Yoga Center at Levy Park. Admission: Free.

title: Oktoberfest at Flying Saucer Sugar Land
address: 15929 City Walk Sugar Land, TX 77478 United States
body: Prost to Oktoberfest week! Each day we will feature a different brewery’s Oktoberfest beer and stein. The brews and glassware go on sale at 7 p.m. everyday.

title: Open Mic Tuesdays at Onyx Artifacts
address: 1802 Yale St Houston, TX 77004 United States
body: It's that time again! Calling all poets, singers, comedians, musicians and open mic night lovers! Open Mic Tuesdays at OA! Sign up by 7:30pm, performances will begin at 8pm! Plenty of coffee, tea, and little bites for the night will be served. Contact us at blackpad15@gmail.com or onyxartifacts.com if you have questions. Admission: Free.

title: Taco Tuezday at Aloft Downtown Houston
address: 820 Fannin St Houston, Texas 77002 United States
body: Who doesn't love a good taco, especially on a Tuezday. Well, check us out. $2 Tacos, $3 Tequila Sunrizez, and $4 Margaritas.

title: Describe the Night at the University of Houston Quintero Theatre
body: Check out the world premiere of Describe the Night, a play that tells the story of men and women, spies, conspiracy theories, and the ever onward passage of time. Admission: $65.

title: The Bayou City Showcase Songwriters Night at The Americana
address: 2957 Bingle Rd. Houston, TX 77055 United States
body: A gathering of local, regional, and sometimes traveling, songwriters performing in an acoustic open mic format. All are welcome to participate and/or listen. Full bar and food available. This is a long-standing series that began in the Montrose and Heights area of Houston. It has recently found a permanent home at The Americana in Spring Branch. Mark Zeus hosts. Admission: Free.

title: The Secret Group Presents: Comedy Open Mic at Boondocks
body: Every week, Boondocks hosts Houston's drunkest open mic. There's a giant patio for smoking, the bartenders are really stingy with the mixers (they make up for it with liquor), and there's a good mix of comics. Hosted by Nathaniel Potts and Cason Nile. Admission: Free.

title: Marvel Legacy Launch Party & Sale at Bedrock City
address: 6516 Westheimer Rd. Houston, TX 77057 United States
body: To coincide with the kickoff of "Marvel Legacy", Bedrock City is hosting a midnight launch party and sale! In addition to exclusive promotional materials and variant covers, we will be hosting other exciting events at the party – including a huge sale, raffle prizes, free food/drinks, and more! Admission: Free.
